idge, MA, before 1648."],"variants":[{"name":"Whitemore","meanings":["English (Somerset): variant of   Whitmore  ."]},{"name":"Whittemore","meanings":["English (Bedfordshire): variant of   Whitmore  .","History: Thomas Whittemore came from England to Charlestown, MA, in or <i>c.</i> 1639. Amos Whittemore, born in Cambridge, MA, in 1759 was an inventor and gunsmith, and another Thomas Whittemore was born in Boston in 1800; he was a Universalist clergyman and MA legislator."]},{"name":"Whitmer","meanings":["English: variant of   Whitmore  .","Americanized form of German   Wittmeyer   or of   Wittmer  ."]},{"name":"Whitmarsh","meanings":["English: habitational name from Whitemarsh, a place in the parish of Sedgehill, Wiltshire, named from Old English <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’ (i.e. ‘phosphorescent’) + <i>mersc</i> ‘marsh’. Compare   Whitmore  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John Whitmore de Caunton was born in 1309, in Caunton, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir David Caunton. He had at least 1 daughter with Joan de Caunton. He died in 1335, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 26."},"et":{"1309–1335":"1309–1335","1309–Female":"1309–Surnud","1308–1322":"1308–1322","1335–1368":"1335–1368","1283–Male":"1283–Surnud","1335":"1335","1368":"1368","1322":"1322","1283":"1283","1309":"1309","1308":"1308","Caunton, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Caunton, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","West Markham, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Markham Clinton, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1309–1335":"1309–1335","1309–Female":"1309–Kuollut","1308–1322":"1308–1322","1335–1368":"1335–1368","1283–Male":"1283–Kuollut","1335":"1335","1368":"1368","1322":"1322","1283":"1283","1309":"1309","1308":"1308","Caunton, Nottinghamshire, En